/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/interaction-design/skills/state-machine/SKILL.md\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/interaction-design/skills/feedback-patterns/SKILL.md\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/interaction-design/skills/form-design/SKILL.md","metadata":{"count":96,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main","time":{"start":1782382651603,"end":1782382651626}},"id":"prt_efe48e47f001qgBJ2Q6jnWiofg","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","messageID":"msg_efe48cf48001lPnL5vZLCG95XK"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782382652114,"sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","part":{"id":"prt_efe48eacf001H7nNIhikPOAfDH","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"74114bc6b1d0355d2e2233e02e3bb18be03224e5","messageID":"msg_efe48cf48001lPnL5vZLCG95XK","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":100825,"input":1386,"output":111,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":99328}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1782382656543,"sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","part":{"id":"prt_efe48fc19001jRFeRZfgUp5bXf","messageID":"msg_efe48ec78001Te4fJfIeJJJELK","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","snapshot":"74114bc6b1d0355d2e2233e02e3bb18be03224e5","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782382668960,"sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"sequential_thinking_sequentialthinking","callID":"tool_xNdMmnbVpmhpuEVf45nrJ148","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"thought":"I need to execute a deep-research lineage for the kimi27 executor. The deliverable is a decision-ready recommendation for restructuring sk-design-interface into a parent skill sk-design with 4-7 focused children, plus structural-model evidence and backward-compatibility implications. I have already read the deep-research skill protocol, the spec/plan/tasks, the existing skills (sk-design-interface, sk-design-md-generator), the apple-bento-grid skill, the deep-loop-workflows hub, sk-code, and the designer-skills-main inventory (9 plugins, 97 skills). I still need to read a sample of the 41 standalone external design-skill docs to cluster them. I should now initialize the lineage state and then run 7 iterations, each with a single focus, reading relevant corpus files and updating state. Finally synthesize research.md. Key questions: (1) What is the optimal 4-7 child taxonomy? (2) Hub-vs-umbrella structural model? (3) How to fold existing skills into children with backward compatibility?","thoughtNumber":1,"totalThoughts":5,"nextThoughtNeeded":true},"output":"{\"thoughtNumber\":1,\"totalThoughts\":5,\"nextThoughtNeeded\":true,\"branches\":[],\"thoughtHistoryLength\":1}","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1782382668949,"end":1782382668958}},"id":"prt_efe491971001TWJ4Xq47f66Yv7","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","messageID":"msg_efe48ec78001Te4fJfIeJJJELK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782382677852,"sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"sequential_thinking_sequentialthinking","callID":"tool_D2fnko9DNpV5jg99u6uRzNRZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"thought":"Iteration plan: Iteration 1 — initialize and survey the designer-skills-main plugin structure and the standalone docs to build a coarse taxonomy. Iteration 2 — deep-read the visual/stylistic standalone docs (taste, delight, polish, soft, bolder, brutalist, minimalist, colorize, oklch) to define a 'design-taste' or 'visual-style' child. Iteration 3 — read layout/structure docs (layout, grid, bento, spacing, responsive, visual-hierarchy) and define a 'design-layout' child. Iteration 4 — read motion/animation docs (animate, morphing-icons, mastering-animate-presence, fixing-motion-performance, 12-principles, micro-interaction-spec) to define a 'design-motion' child. Iteration 5 — read interface/critique/ux docs (interaction-design, make-interfaces-feel-better, fixing-accessibility, critique, audit, clarify, adapt, distill) to define 'design-interface' and 'design-critique' children. Iteration 6 — analyze existing internal skills and structural model evidence (deep-loop-workflows hub vs umbrella, sk-code, sk-design-md-generator) to decide hub/umbrella and backward compatibility. Iteration 7 — refine taxonomy boundaries, source assignments, and converge. Then synthesis.","thoughtNumber":2,"totalThoughts":5,"nextThoughtNeeded":true},"output":"{\"thoughtNumber\":2,\"totalThoughts\":5,\"nextThoughtNeeded\":true,\"branches\":[],\"thoughtHistoryLength\":2}","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1782382677845,"end":1782382677851}},"id":"prt_efe492c970017uYIrEXLHNTU9x","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","messageID":"msg_efe48ec78001Te4fJfIeJJJELK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782382681511,"sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"sequential_thinking_sequentialthinking","callID":"tool_mHOcCXXSAjqc8ZvehnPvknJR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"thought":"State files to create in phase_init: deep-research-config.json, deep-research-state.jsonl (config record), deep-research-strategy.md, findings-registry.json, dashboard. The artifact_dir is .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/lineages/kimi27. Use canonical names. The config should include topic, maxIterations:7, convergenceThreshold:0.05, stuckThreshold:3, specFolder, sessionId, executor info, lineage label, resource_map_present:false (no resource-map.md at spec folder? Actually spec folder doesn't have resource-map.md; only research dir has fanout config). No existing state so fresh. Also create iterations/ subdir.","thoughtNumber":3,"totalThoughts":5,"nextThoughtNeeded":true},"output":"{\"thoughtNumber\":3,\"totalThoughts\":5,\"nextThoughtNeeded\":true,\"branches\":[],\"thoughtHistoryLength\":3}","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1782382681505,"end":1782382681510}},"id":"prt_efe494f5700121PwpHvn4R6i7i","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","messageID":"msg_efe48ec78001Te4fJfIeJJJELK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782382687099,"sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"sequential_thinking_sequentialthinking","callID":"tool_78jnAqv8GDR40LEN7Gx04eXg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"thought":"For structural model evidence, the deep-loop-workflows hub is a strong precedent for 'single hub with nested mode packets': one SKILL.md hub, mode-registry.json, one graph-metadata.json at hub, and per-mode packets with their own SKILL.md/references but no graph-metadata. This keeps advisor discovery as one skill while allowing per-mode convergence/state. The umbrella-router-over-sibling-family model would have each child as a top-level skill with its own graph-metadata.json and a separate router skill; the skill advisor would surface multiple skills. For sk-design, because the existing sk-design-interface is already a discoverable skill and sk-design-md-generator is a sibling, the umbrella model risks fragmenting the advisor surface. The hub model aligns with deep-loop-workflows and lets the parent own the family boundary. However, the umbrella may be better if children need independent release/ownership or if the parent would become too large. Evidence from sk-code shows a single broad skill with internal surface routing, not a parent of siblings. Evidence from sk-design-md-generator's family boundary statement ('extraction and format-fidelity engine of the sk-design-* family') suggests the family already exists in intent.","thoughtNumber":4,"totalThoughts":5,"nextThoughtNeeded":true},"output":"{\"thoughtNumber\":4,\"totalThoughts\":5,\"nextThoughtNeeded\":true,\"branches\":[],\"thoughtHistoryLength\":4}","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1782382687093,"end":1782382687098}},"id":"prt_efe495da3001i8i1j6qjTmhftn","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","messageID":"msg_efe48ec78001Te4fJfIeJJJELK"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782382691365,"sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"sequential_thinking_sequentialthinking","callID":"tool_IMk5bcOcohYgR90lZIQbP9Bj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"thought":"Backward compatibility: sk-design-interface can become a mode packet under sk-design (e.g., sk-design/interface or sk-design/sk-design-interface) while keeping its existing triggers and graph metadata as an alias. To avoid breaking existing references, the parent SKILL.md can route to it as the 'interface direction' child. sk-design-md-generator can similarly be folded as 'design-system-extract' or 'design-reference' child; its pipeline is distinct (URL extraction) and should remain a child. Onboarding implications: each child needs its own SKILL.md, references, feature catalog, manual tests; the parent needs a mode-registry.json or family-registry.json and one graph-metadata.json. The parent's description should encompass the family. Existing skills' references can be moved verbatim into child packets, repointing internal paths. The parent hub must stay logic-free and not duplicate per-child convergence or state.","thoughtNumber":5,"totalThoughts":5,"nextThoughtNeeded":false},"output":"{\"thoughtNumber\":5,\"totalThoughts\":5,\"nextThoughtNeeded\":false,\"branches\":[],\"thoughtHistoryLength\":5}","metadata":{"truncated":false},"title":"","time":{"start":1782382691359,"end":1782382691364}},"id":"prt_efe497376001yDYUhoETsThEZl","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","messageID":"msg_efe48ec78001Te4fJfIeJJJELK"}}
