ouse-template SKILL.md routes to the full principles in references/design-process/design_principles.md. The skill is Apache-2.0 only: the design principles are unchanged vendored Apache content and LICENSE.txt is its single license. The aesthetic inventory can be sourced live from a real design system you own, used as either reuse-ground (reuse its tokens and components before generating) or critique-against (name the closest realized default, then deviate). Exactly one system is resolved from the subject, never a chooser, and nothing is cached into the skill, which keeps it free of any third party license burden. The objective quality floor stays authored in references/design-process/ux_quality_reference.md as paraphrased non-copyrightable facts. When a brief asks for two or more directions, references/design-process/variation_diversity.md applies a seed-of-thought debias so the set is not N safe copies of the median: a committed random seed picks a non-median start in a subject-grounded option space and the rest are spread to be distinct, with grounding and the anti-default critique still primary and never a style chooser. The skill ships a feature_catalog/ and a manual_testing_playbook/ for sk-doc alignment.\",\n    \"source_docs\": [\n      \"SKILL.md\",\n      \"README.md\",\n      \"references/design-process/design_principles.md\",\n      \"LICENSE.txt\"\n    ],\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-06-13T00:00:00Z\",\n    \"last_updated_at\": \"2026-06-14T14:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":154,"totalLines":154,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-design-interface/graph-metadata.json","time":{"start":1782386030695,"end":1782386030709}},"id":"prt_efe7c7645001dUecjPb2zvUPIM","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","messageID":"msg_efe7c5172001wNBAYAlvmeiRo0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782386031340,"sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"tool_rqaKRvf8M93MNWH9BMxSWi7s","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/graph-metadata.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/graph-metadata.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"schema_version\": 2,\n3:   \"skill_id\": \"sk-design-md-generator\",\n4:   \"family\": \"sk-code\",\n5:   \"category\": \"design\",\n6:   \"edges\": {\n7:     \"depends_on\": [],\n8:     \"enhances\": [\n9:       {\n10:         \"target\": \"sk-code\",\n11:         \"weight\": 0.4,\n12:         \"context\": \"The extracted DESIGN.md is the implementation contract sk-code builds against - verbatim colours, type, spacing, shadows, radii\"\n13:       }\n14:     ],\n15:     \"siblings\": [\n16:       {\n17:         \"target\": \"sk-design-interface\",\n18:         \"weight\": 0.55,\n19:         \"context\": \"Design-family pair: this skill captures an existing site's real design system; sk-design-interface invents new distinctive direction\"\n20:       },\n21:       {\n22:         \"target\": \"mcp-figma\",\n23:         \"weight\": 0.45,\n24:         \"context\": \"Sibling design-extraction tool sourcing from Figma Desktop instead of a live URL, with a DESIGN.md output overlap\"\n25:       },\n26:       {\n27:         \"target\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n28:         \"weight\": 0.45,\n29:         \"context\": \"Sibling design tool sourcing from Open Design projects; this skill is the live-URL extraction path\"\n30:       }\n31:     ],\n32:     \"conflicts_with\": [],\n33:     \"prerequisite_for\": []\n34:   },\n35:   \"manual\": {\n36:     \"depends_on\": [],\n37:     \"related_to\": [\n38:       \"sk-design-interface\",\n39:       \"mcp-figma\",\n40:       \"mcp-open-design\",\n41:       \"sk-code\"\n42:     ]\n43:   },\n44:   \"domains\": [\n45:     \"design-systems\",\n46:     \"design-tokens\",\n47:     \"css-extraction\",\n48:     \"design-to-markdown\",\n49:     \"web-design-capture\",\n50:     \"design-reference\"\n51:   ],\n52:   \"intent_signals\": [\n53:     \"extract design system\",\n54:     \"generate DESIGN.md\",\n55:     \"capture website css\",\n56:     \"design tokens from url\",\n57:     \"create design reference\",\n58:     \"design-to-markdown\",\n59:     \"anti-hallucination design doc\",\n60:     \"extract design tokens\"\n61:   ],\n62:   \"derived\": {\n63:     \"trigger_phrases\": [\n64:       \"extract design system\",\n65:       \"generate design.md\",\n66:       \"capture website css\",\n67:       \"design tokens from url\",\n68:       \"create design reference\",\n69:       \"design-to-markdown\",\n70:       \"extract design tokens\"\n71:     ],\n72:     \"key_topics\": [\n73:       \"live-website CSS extraction into a v3 Style Reference DESIGN.md\",\n74:       \"three-phase pipeline: extract (Playwright) -> write -> validate\",\n75:       \"verbatim-value cardinal rule (no estimated/invented tokens)\",\n76:       \"6-digit lowercase hex and L1-L4 stability classification\",\n77:       \"tokens.json output at output/<domain>/ and validate.ts fidelity check\",\n78:       \"gold-standard examples (stripe/vercel/linear/supabase)\",\n79:       \"self-contained TypeScript pipeline embedded under backend/\"\n80:     ],\n81:     \"intent_signals\": [\n82:       \"design system extraction\",\n83:       \"DESIGN.md generator\",\n84:       \"css token extraction\",\n85:       \"design tokens from url\",\n86:       \"design reference\",\n87:       \"design-to-markdown\"\n88:     ],\n89:     \"key_files\": [\n90:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/SKILL.md\",\n91:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/README.md\",\n92:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n93:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/references/extraction_workflow.md\",\n94:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/references/troubleshooting.md\",\n95:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md\",\n96:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/references/design_md_format.md\",\n97:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/assets/design_md_prompt_template.md\",\n98:       \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/assets/cardinal_rules_card.md\"\n99:     ],\n100:     \"entities\": [\n101:       {\n102:         \"name\": \"sk-design-md-generator\",\n103:         \"kind\": \"skill\",\n104:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/SKILL.md\",\n105:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n106:       },\n107:       {\n108:         \"name\": \"README\",\n109:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n110:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/README.md\",\n111:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n112:       },\n113:       {\n114:         \"name\": \"INSTALL_GUIDE\",\n115:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n116:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n117:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n118:       },\n119:       {\n120:         \"name\": \"extraction_workflow\",\n121:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n122:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/references/extraction_workflow.md\",\n123:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n124:       },\n125:       {\n126:         \"name\": \"troubleshooting\",\n127:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n128:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/references/troubleshooting.md\",\n129:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n130:       },\n131:       {\n132:         \"name\": \"design_md_prompt_template\",\n133:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n134:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/assets/design_md_prompt_template.md\",\n135:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n136:       },\n137:       {\n138:         \"name\": \"cardinal_rules_card\",\n139:         \"kind\": \"reference\",\n140:         \"path\": \".opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/assets/cardinal_rules_card.md\",\n141:         \"source\": \"derived\"\n142:       }\n143:     ],\n144:     \"causal_summary\": \"sk-design-md-generator captures a live website's real, measured CSS into a publication-quality v3 Style Reference DESIGN.md so AI agents build against ground truth instead of hallucinating colours, fonts, spacing, and shadows. It ships an embedded TypeScript pipeline under backend/ that runs a three-phase pipeline: EXTRACT (a Playwright crawler samples five viewports and emits output/<domain>/tokens.json with every token tagged a 4-layer stability class), WRITE (the agent composes the v3 Style Reference DESIGN.md copying every numeric value verbatim from tokens.json, 6-digit lowercase hex, L1+L2 in main sections, L3 marked subject-to-change, L4 excluded; the value-bearing sections are pre-rendered deterministically, so the agent writes prose only), and VALIDATE (validate.ts checks hex accuracy and section completeness). The cardinal rule is verbatim fidelity: a value that is estimated, rounded, or invented breaks the document's whole reason to exist. It is the extraction-and-format-fidelity engine of the sk-design-* family - sibling to sk-design-interface (which invents new distinctive direction) and the mcp-figma / mcp-open-design transports (which source from Figma and Open Design rather than live URLs) - and its DESIGN.md is the implementation contract sk-code builds against. Setup is a one-time cd backend && npm install && npx playwright install chromium.\",\n145:     \"source_docs\": [\n146:       \"SKILL.md\",\n147:       \"README.md\",\n148:       \"INSTALL_GUIDE.md\",\n149:       \"references/extraction_workflow.md\",\n150:       \"references/troubleshooting.md\",\n151:       \"changelog/v1.0.0.0.md\",\n152:       \"assets/design_md_prompt_template.md\",\n153:       \"assets/cardinal_rules_card.md\"\n154:     ],\n155:     \"created_at\": \"2026-06-21T10:00:00Z\",\n156:     \"last_updated_at\": \"2026-06-21T10:00:00Z\"\n157:   }\n158: }\n\n(End of file - total 158 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"schema_version\": 2,\n  \"skill_id\": \"sk-design-md-generator\",\n  \"family\": \"sk-code\",\n  \"category\": \"design\",\n  \"edges\": {\n    \"depends_on\": [],\n    \"enhances\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-code\",\n        \"weight\": 0.4,\n        \"context\": \"The extracted DESIGN.md is the implementation contract sk-code builds against - verbatim colours, type, spacing, shadows, radii\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"siblings\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-design-interface\",\n        \"weight\": 0.55,\n        \"context\": \"Design-family pair: this skill captures an existing site's real design system; sk-design-interface invents new distinctive direction\"\n      },","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design-md-generator/graph-metadata.json","text":"{\n  \"schema_version\": 2,\n  \"skill_id\": \"sk-design-md-generator\",\n  \"family\": \"sk-code\",\n  \"category\": \"design\",\n  \"edges\": {\n    \"depends_on\": [],\n    \"enhances\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-code\",\n        \"weight\": 0.4,\n        \"context\": \"The extracted DESIGN.md is the implementation contract sk-code builds against - verbatim colours, type, spacing, shadows, radii\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"siblings\": [\n      {\n        \"target\": \"sk-design-interface\",\n        \"weight\": 0.55,\n        \"context\": \"Design-family pair: this skill captures an existing site's real design system; sk-design-interface invents new distinctive direction\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"target\": \"mcp-figma\",\n        \"weight\": 0.45,\n        \"context\": \"Sibling design-extraction tool sourcing from Figma Desktop instead of a live URL, with a DESIGN.md output overlap\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"target\": \"mcp-open-design\",\n        \"weight\": 0.45,\n        \"context\": \"Sibling design tool sourcing from Open Design projects; this skill is the live-URL extraction path\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"conflicts_with\": [],\n    \"prerequisite_for\": []\n  },\n  \"manual\": {\n    \"depends_on\": [],\n    \"related_to\": [\n      \"sk-design-interface\",\n      \"mcp-figma\",\n      \"mcp-open-design\",\n      \"sk-code\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"domains\": [\n    \"design-systems\",\n    \"design-tokens\",\n    \"css-extraction\",\n    \"design-to-markdown\",\n    \"web-design-capture\",\n    \"design-reference\"\n  ],\n  \"intent_signals\": [\n    \"extract design system\",\n    \"generate DESIGN.md\",\n    \"capture website css\",\n    \"design tokens from url\",\n    \"create design reference\",\n    \"design-to-markdown\",\n    \"anti-hallucination design doc\",\n    \"extract design tokens\"\n  ],\n  \"derived\": {\n    \"trigger_phrases\": [\n      \"extract design system\",\n      \"generate design.md\",\n      \"capture website css\",\n      \"design tokens from url\",\n      \"create design reference\",\n      \"design-to-markdown\",\n      \"extract design tokens\"\n    ],\n    \"key_topics\": [\n      \"live-website CSS extraction into a v3 Style Reference DESIGN.md\",\n      \"three-phase pipeline: extract (Playwright) -> write -> validate\",\n      \"verbatim-value cardinal rule (no estimated/invented tokens)\",\n      \"6-digit lowercase hex and L1-L4 stability classification\",\n      \"tokens.json output at output/<domain>/ and validate.ts fidelity check\",\n      \"gold-standard examples (stripe/vercel/linear/supabase)\",\n      \"self-contained TypeScript pipeline embedded under backend/\"\n    ],\n    \"intent_signals\": [\n      \"design system extraction\",\n      \"DESIGN.md generator\",\n      \"css token extractio