the minimal onboarding/back-compat path for each child?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n  \"keyFindings\": [],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": []\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/lineages/kimi27/deep-research-findings-registry.json","text":"{\n  \"openQuestions\": [\n    \"Which 4-7 child skills best cover the corpus while keeping each child sharply bounded?\",\n    \"Which corpus sources feed each child, and where do boundaries prevent overlap?\",\n    \"Does the parent use a hub-with-nested-packets model or an umbrella-router-over-siblings model, and what evidence supports the choice?\",\n    \"How do the existing sk-design-interface and sk-design-md-generator skills map into children without losing their current trigger coverage?\",\n    \"What is the minimal onboarding/back-compat path for each child?\"\n  ],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n  \"keyFindings\": [],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": []\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":12,"totalLines":12,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/lineages/kimi27/deep-research-findings-registry.json","time":{"start":1782386402503,"end":1782386402508}},"id":"prt_efe82209a001bcBE6C1ghjrmjg","sessionID":"ses_101b8caf5ffeN4H3YS4hZhe6E8","messageID":"msg_efe8205c3001qzmP39IcBrr0PL"}}
